    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against required level 3, reflecting single quasi-static test condition per ASTM F1717 protocol. This gap is accepted given that (a) ASTM F1717 is the recognized consensus standard for this device type, (b) all quantitative validation criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are met across all three QoIs, and (c) model risk level 3 with medium decision consequence does not require dynamic or environmental condition coverage for this submission context. Residual uncertainty acknowledged in submission documentation.",
